The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Matthaeus confirms trip
                                                                                                                       7                                      Matthaeus confirms trip
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Germanys World Cup winning captain Lothar Matthaeus has confirmed his presence at a city hotel on January 15 during the unveiling ceremony of the Fifa World Cup organised by Coca Cola.         
	Fans will get a lifetime opportunity to meet the football legend in person and see the solid 18-carat gold trophy which is being brought to India for the first time, organisers of the tour stated. The trophy will be displayed at Yuba Bharati Krirangan for three days.                                                                                                                     
